      "content": [
        {
          "type": "theory",
          "data": {
            "title": "New mark: ះ (Ah) — short, sharp stop",
            "text": "This vowel mark makes the sound SHORT and SHARP.\n\nIt's like adding a full stop to the vowel.\n\nCompare:\n- កា = kaa (long, open)\n- កះ = kah (short, stops abruptly)\n\nMoon team works the same way:\n- គា = kea (long)\n- គះ = keah (short)\n\nThe pattern is consistent: the vowel mark changes the LENGTH and QUALITY, but the consonant still controls the TEAM color.",
            "sublesson_title": "The Ah Mark"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "quiz",
          "data": {
            "question": "Read the syllable: What is ក + ះ (Ah mark) in Sun series?",
            "options": [
              "kah (short)",
              "kaa (long)",
              "keah",
              "kam"
            ],
            "correct_answer": "kah (short)",
            "explanation": "Sun letters keep vowels clean. ះ makes a short, sharp stop.\nSo: កះ = kah (short)"
          }
        },
